esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when container memory usage exceeds 95% of its limit or node allocation.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Containers consuming more than 95% of memory limits — OOM risk.
//
// Action needed:
// Increase memory limits, check for memory leaks, review workload patterns.
//
// Adjust threshold as needed (e.g., 0.9 for 90% early warning).
TS metrics-kubernetes.container-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.container.memory.usage.limit.pct` > 0.95
  OR `kubernetes.container.memory.usage.node.pct` > 0.95
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.container.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
